Title: 2002 Acura RSX-S
Description:
Up for sale is a 2002 Acura RSX-S / RSX Type-S.
Got it roughly 2 years ago and looking to let go of it as I am moving back to the city and have no use for a car.
6-speed stick shift, just under 149000 miles on the odometer, will go up as I still use it for errands before moving.
A/C does not work, but the heat still works fine.
SRS light is on for code 22-1, Open or increased resistance in passenger seat belt buckle tensioner. Seat belts are covered under lifetime warranty from Acura.
Car is not in perfect physical condition, has some rust spots. Please refer to pictures.
Car came with AEM Short Ram Intake and was lowered when I bought it. I believe it is lowered on Ksport Kontrol Pro Coilovers.

Work done since I got it: (i have receipts for some of the work done)
- Replaced tires with new Michelins Primacy MXM4s (done at ~144k miles)
- Replaced exhaust with a new stainless steel exhaust (https://www.yonaka.com/Yonaka_Acura_RSX_Type_S_Catback_Exhaust_System_p/ymcb-rsx-s.htm)
- Replaced clutch with OEM clutch (done at ~144k miles)
- Replaced master and slave clutch cylinders
- Replaced Valve Cover Gasket and downstream O2 sensor
- Replaced oil pressure switch and front axle seal
- Replaced rear tie-rod ends

Stuff that needs to be fixed/replaced:
- Front and rear sway bar links
- A/C Compressor, Evaporator, Drier (to get AC working)
- Calibration of hand/parking brake
- Driver and passenger door lock actuators (I have the parts but never got around to replacing them)
- VTEC solenoid might need replacing (VTEC isn't engaging)

$2700 cash only no trades

Description:

Title: 6MT 2012 Audi A4 Quattro Prestige S-Line
Description:
I am the 3rd Owner of this Rarely Optioned Monsoon Grey Audi A4, w/ 6 Speed Manual Transmission, 2.0 turbo TSFI. Oil has been changed every 5,000mi w/ factory recommended Castrol Euro Formula Oil since I purchased the vehicle. I have documented all services since the vehicle has been in my possession. CARFAX shows all previous maintenance, car had been serviced at the dealer its entire life until the CPO extended warranty expired in 2016. 

Vehicle is solid and needs nothing, services are up to date, drives perfectly, engine, transmission and clutch are all in perfect working order. Car has a clean CARFAX, never in an accident. Currently sitting on Premium 19" RS4 Style Wheels, with Continental Contact 3 tires, tires have over 70% of tread left. Car handles all Chicago driving conditions without hesitation, snow is especially notable, Audi's Quattro system is truly exceptional. Vehicle features S-Line trim w/ Prestige package, which includes sport-tuned suspension, upgraded driver and passenger sports seats (extremely comfortable and rare), upgraded exterior appearance package, including front and rear bumpers, S-Line badges and Door Sills. This car is fully optioned, options available beyond what this car features would only be available by upgrading to an S4. Please note, an S4 of similar age, features and miles blue books over $20k.

Noteworthy features are as follows:

*RARE 6 Speed Manual Transmission

The Revo Stage 1 Tune raises horsepower to roughly 260hp and torque to right about 300lb ft. The tune, paired with the manual transmission balance this car very well, smooth, responsive power in every gear.

Title: 1992 Chevrolet Corvette
Description: 1992 Chevrolet Corvette Coupe.  5.7 liter LT-1 Modified, with 6 speed Transmission. 30 over 355ci motor with Scat forged Crankshaft, GM LT-4 Hot cam kit with Crane 1.6 Rockers, Light weight stainless steel under cut valves. Race ported heads, up graded ignition to 1996 LT-4 with New Optispark. Upgraded throttle body to BBK 52mm and SLP intake kit with 3 K&N Air filters......this baby sucks a lot of air! Exhaust is Hooker 2151 long tube Ceramic coated Headers into True 3" duals flowing into a Stainless Borla Cat-Back system with dual inter-cooled square tips. Carolina stage 3 Race Clutch with Kevlar pucks attached to a Fidanza Lightweight Flywheel..........The light weight flywheel allows the engine to rev/spool very quickly. Acceleration from a dead stop is.......unbelievable! Koni 3 way adjustable shocks compliment the ride. Stopping is provided by ZR-1 Brake Calipers with 13" Slotted and drilled rotors with Carbotech disc pads all the way around. Braided steel lines on front calipers. The shifter was upgraded to the B&M Short Throw Shifter, nice solid shift with 80% less movement. All this is sitting on  New Goodyear Tires. Body is Burgandy Pearl with Black Leather Interior. Could use an interior kit. Showing wear on driver side. This has been a great car but I don't drive it much anymore, just stays in storage.........time for someone else to enjoy it......217 369 7144

Title: 2007 Mini Cooper
Description:
So in the spirit of classic used car salesmanship, I will now do my best to convince you why your life will be (insert exaggerated number) percent better if you were to be rolling around in this road legal go-kart for grown ups. 

There are plenty of cars out there that you can immediately tell the type of person who's driving them (particularly giant lifted trucks (lol)). However, man or woman, young or old, Donald, Hillary or Bernie, this car somehow has no social demographic and everyone with a beating heart can have a good time driving it. If you're looking for something fun to get groceries in, you've found it. If you want something quick and nimble to get away from the cops in during your next bank heist, look no further (payment in non sequential bills if this is you). This little piece of English rally car history has a little something everyone can appreciate. From its' unique take on classic styling, to its' tight and responsive steering, it'll make even a devout nihilist believe they have found a purpose. 

Not convinced??? Well, how about some Pros and Cons???

Pros:

-Really low miles for the year
-Leather seats
-Well maintained and clean interior (it's my girlfriend's car, and she's meticulously, if not annoyingly clean)
-Push manual with paddle shifters (it has get-away car potential) 
-Fresh brake pads
-Mark Wahlberg, Jason Statham and Charlize Theron all looked awesome in the Italian Job remake (they also got away).
-It's a sporty, yet practical car that fits anyone (even Jason Statham)
-Great MPG

Cons:

-You cannot transport lumber 
-Not enough room to transport a family of 12 (possibly 10 with limited leg room)
-It unfortunately does not have an autopilot feature for casual car napping
-It beeps at you to change gears sometimes (actual con, I'll shift when I want to car)


If you're interested in this little mean machine, feel free to email me, or text me at (217) Forr Wan Sehhven Nine Phore Cix Cix. I picked this price because it is the average between the kelly blue book value for 'very good' and 'good'. That being said, it's my girlfriend's car and she has given me permission to be negotiable. So if you think you have a fair offer, worst I can do is say "how about this instead"

Title: 1998 Honda Prelude Type SH
Description:
Well most pleasant greetings to you, casual craigslist car connoisseurs who's stumbled upon this post. Let me give you the quick reason why this car is so great, and no, it's not because of me. I got ridiculously lucky when I found this car on craigslist a couple years ago. The man I bought it from was the first and only owner, it had just shy of 100k on it, and this man took meticulous care of it. Meticulous to the point where the interior was, and is still in, suspiciously good shape (he may have been a warlock, I'm just guessing here). Meticulous to the point where he gave me, what seems to be, every single receipt for every single service checkup that was ever done to this fine piece of eastern machinery. So you'll inherit that lovely 20 year car biography neatly tucked away in the glove box upon purchasing. 

You may have also seen my recent post for my matte black 350z (because I guess I only need one four door now? For some unknown reason?), I'm bringing this up because I bought this car so I'd have a sporty and reliable car to drive around to save miles on my Z (and also because... more Japanese sports cars is always better). Ironically, I kinda fell in love with this car really fast, so I of course had to buy more cars to save miles on this car. This love also encouraged me to get this baby looking like the gorgeous Blasian super model you now see. Not saying she wasn't hot before she met me, but she's defiantly getting more looks now than ever. Styles change, and she was still wearing a coat from the 90s. So I methodically fixed all the little cosmetic issues that were keeping this long slender Asian princess from getting the respect she deserved, and then took her shopping to pick out a sleek 3m matte black dress to give her more of the 21st century sports car look she wanted so badly (treat your ladies gentleman, they deserve it). 

 Unfortunately, now, at the old and decrepit age of 23, it seems as though my ascension into adulthood has come with a collection of hefty prices. Prices that are clearing out my damn garage. But I've rambled enough. Here's the goods:

-DOHC VTEC - it still pumps power and ticks like clockwork
-Sport breaks - because the VTEC will obviously kill you otherwise
-Really well maintained interior - because of a possible warlock
-Blutooth and Phone connectivity - New Sony head unit to utilize the sound system, and hands free blah blah blah
-Bumping sound system - It's legitimately surprising how great the speakers are, 
-Sparco Shift Knob - I'm keeping the original shift knob to remember how great I had it once, everything else on the car is its' original part.
-Working everything - Please keep it that way if you buy it, it's a small miracle.

I'm fairly certain there is only one goofy problem with the car I could never figure out. The driver's side window controls only work when the door is open. It's like there's a wire that just doesn't quite connect when the door is shut, but when it's open, everything is absolutely fine. It's just a miniscule inconvenience at a drive through, but if popping the door before you order your big mac is your breaking point, then I guess I'm so sorry for wasting your time (that's me being facetious). 

Anywho, I'm Tony, and if you're interested in purchasing my Prelude to indirectly help me finance the payments to the financial institutions whom helped me finance my finance degree, then feel free to give me a text at (Too Wan Sehven) PhOOr Wun SeHVvan - NEIN fore CiXX CiXX. Or email me. But let's be honest here, you're not gonna email me. I priced it based on the other Preludes in the market and the KBB price. I'm friendly and negotiable, so respect me, and I'll respect you right on back.

Side note, I'd love to get my offer price, but if you offer exactly 4200 in cash, I will immediately accept with no negotiations... because it's hilarious.

Title: 1996 Impala SS
Description: Up for sale I have a clean 1996 Impala SS. This is a performance sedan made by Chevrolet in '94-96. The 96 is different as it has analog gauges and a floor shifter, the only year these were made with them. It has the all original drivetrain with a LT1 5.7 V8, and a four speed automatic with overdrive 4l60e. It runs and drives strong. The only things that have been done to it mechanically wise are a new, larger Mishimoto radiator to prevent infamous LT1 overheating, a belt tensioner pully as the original started to squeak, MSD plugs and wires, and a K&N cold air induction kit. It also has a converter-back Pypes 2.5 inch exhaust paired with Black Widow Venom 250 mufflers, providing a strong yet quieter drive sound. Inside the interior is also all original, and the carpets are showing stain as pictured. I'm sure a good enough shampoo job could get most of it up. The dash also has sun stain, as does the steering wheel. All four speakers have been replaced, with Kickers in the back and Pioneer in the front. The exterior has minor dings and scratches, I pictured the majority. The clear coat is otherwise perfect, as is the Dark Cherry Metallic paint. This is a perfect daily driver, and would be a great first vehicle. I drive it to school and back every week day, so the 125xxx miles will rise. $7500 FIRM. Please text, I am unlikely to answer calls and won't check any emails. Don't message me from Craigslist. Cash only, won't ship. Don't need help selling. Clean title in hand. Trade for 5.3 Silverado that isn't ruined.

Title: 2007 350z
Description:
So I bought this bodacious Japanese harbinger of sexual arousal you're looking at when I lived in Miami 4 years ago. Although it had a rebuilt title and the man selling it to me spoke zero English, after inspecting it and driving it I realized apparently "rebuilt" in Spanish also means "bargain", so I bought it on the spot. There are three things you learn to love behind the wheel of this mobile defibrillator: the sound of your own car, how slow 80mph can feel, and the ego boost you get when people break their neck trying to get a double take. Now, I can't promise you that everyone will love it, but I can promise that they will look at it anyway. 

You're probably wondering why I would sell something that can literally get you laid by waving at a beautiful blonde girl you're passing on the highway (yes, that actually happened, I couldn't believe it either, coolest moment of my life). Well in short, it's impossible to steer this car past my throbbing car inspired erection.... Just kidding, I graduated college and I'm apparently supposed to be "responsible" now and "grow up and actually use my 2 business degrees" or some bs like that. Side note, I also moved in with my girlfriend, completely unrelated to that last sentence.... he said sarcastically... 

Anywho, here's what you actually want to know. The goods:

-Upgraded Exhaust (done in Miami, it sounds amazing, it's also the reason the check engine light wont go off fyi)
-Sport front Calipers and Rotors (if you go fast, ya gotta stop fast too)
-Sport Clutch (cuz, duh)
-Sony touch screen head unit (it's got blutooth, usb and aux, it's also sub ready)
-Brand new set of Drift Z Rims and Tires (they both have like 20 miles on them total, you can't have my Lexani rims, sorry)
-Sparco Shift Knob (Literally bought this because I want to keep the old stock knob as a memento, your lucky day)
-Custom front and back bumper (don't hit anything, they were a lot of work to get right dammit)
-Matte Black 3m 1080 M12 car vinyl wrap (because seriously, how awesome does that shit look?)
----The only thing I think is really wrong with the car is a dent in the passenger side door that some asshole left for me. 

I tried to make sure the things I did to the car would make it more awesome, not ricey. I hate ricers, so I hope that you see this as a tasteful, yet maniacally badass car monstrosity. Since I know this will come up, all jokes aside, yes it's a certified rebuilt, I bought it that way in Miami. That being said, rebuilt doesn't mean you get to haggle with me like we're at a Tijuana bracelet stand.  

If you want it, and promise me eye to eye you will take good care of it, I will regretfully barter the car to you in exchange for green rectangles or a certified bank rectangle. 

I'm Tony, number is (ToO-Won-SehVen) PhouR-Wan-Sleven NEIN-Foore-Sixx-Syx. 
If you can read that, feel free to text me, or I check my emails.

***Update - Yes, I'm totally negotiable. The price on the ad is a strategic, yet arbitrarily random number. It isn't firm... Unless you want to pay that number... In which case I will totally take that number.... but only if you insist...
***Update #2 - Unfortunately, I don't want to trade. It's not that I don't like motorcycles, boats, jetskis, lifted trucks, Apache attack choppers and or other asian sports cars. It's just I have too many vehicles as it is, not enough room for them all, and not enough legs and arms to drive them all... that and student loans.... lots of student loans.... soul crippling, car stealing, downright depressing, no default policy having, future economic collapse causing, government organized thievery. And Uncle Sam wants his mother f#$%ing money yesterday.

Title: 2007 Chevrolet Chevy Impala 4dr Sdn 3.9L LT - ALL CREDIT DRIVES TODAY!
(2000) Nissam Maxima SE [Bad Brakes]
Description:
If you are looking for an affordable, reliable vehicle for your leisure, you'd best look elsewhere because this Maxima will come with no such attributes! If you're an up-and-coming mechanic and would like to dabble, this might be for you, though...

As it currently is, this Maxima requires new fron brake pads and rotors, a front brake caliper, and left and right front brake hose replacements--- all of which I'm unwilling to learn to do myself and am absolutely not paying the amount quoted by the mechanic of just a few bucks short of $700.

As well, it has a white paint job with decadent streaks of brown rust which adds jacks**t to its aesthetics. For the incense-lovers out there, the trunk has the slight odor of milk thanks to the roommates of a friend who once had loosely-capped containers of milk in the back that spilled over, (who didn't even have the courtesy to apologize after realizing this, by the way). 

If these are insufficient in offending your senses still, I'd like to take you to the interior which is also not a pleaser for the eyes! Due to a lineage of negligent vehicle owners (including myself, of course), the floors are mucked up and covered with bits of rock and dead leaves, you'd think you were stepping into a state park when you get into this thing for a ride.

On a more serious note, though this car (like myself as a car-owner) is not without its faults, it's gotten me from Chicago to Champaign or vice versa about 15 times in the almost two years I've had it, as well as from campus to the stores on Prospect Ave even more so. It'll definitely get you from A to B, just not every time. I think the highest mileage I had with this car without incident (i.e. something breaking down or in need or repair) was about 1,500 miles. But all I did with the car ws fill the gas, have the oil changed, and refill the under-the-hood fluids when it deserves more care and maintenance, probably.


------------------------------------------


[TL;DR] 

- Needs some brake replacements and repairs. Can't get myself to fix these issues, and after having to deal with many repairs over the course of almost two years of ownership, I'd rather just sell it to someone willing to take care of it. Once the brakes are dealt with, the car will drive well. Otherwise, I'd recommend towing the car, else you'd have to force the car to drive with the brakes clamped down.

-Trunk smells of milk

- The AC works, though it is more refrigerator-cold than freezer-cold.

- The rear left door won't open. Will have to replace the inner locking mechanisms to fix that, which apparently costs a bit in the $300s according to my mechanic.

- Lots of rust on the side skirts and around the rear wheels

- A few dings, scrapes, dents, and a damaged rear-right bumper

Title: 2014 159" Ram Promaster 2500 Full Conversion - high top roof!

It is still under the FACTORY POWERTRAIN WARRANTY until June 2019 (or 100,000 miles)! So you can drive peacefully knowing if anything breaks, Ram will fix it for free! You can see pictures for the actual conversion, but work that went into the van include:

- 340 Watts Solar with 225ah trojan batteries. This is hooked up to an mppt solar charge controller and an 800 watt inverter. Plenty of power to run my laptop, rice cooker, tv and roku!
- Fully insulated with polyiso and foam.
- Day bed that is a twin in its current form, but it also pulls out and can be as big as a king! There is also plenty of storage with 3 long cabinets under the bed! 
- 32" LED monitor mounted to the roof that flips down, hooked up to a roku or a laptop. Perfect for watching a movie while in bed!

I've used this van for stealth urban camping and for extended camping at national parks as well. Its great for both!

Title: 2003 Honda Civic EX Manual Transmission
Description:
Unfortunately, I have chosen to get rid of my beloved 2003 Honda Civic. It is a manual and the engine still runs like a champ. However, it has gotten quite a few issues within the last year or so that caused me to get a newer car to help me in my commute. It is silver, with the hood slightly off color because it is still the primer and I never bothered to paint it. There are no big dents anywhere. 

Currently, the clutch most likely needs replaced, along with the head gasket. It also has an issue with one of the ball joints on one of the tires. The inside is not in the best condition, but also not terrible at all. The gas cap door has an issue that requires you to unlock it through the trunk, but it never hindered me. It also may need a new battery. The tires are relatively new as well. It does have cosmetic damage as it was totaled around four years ago and rebuilt. When it was totaled the only things replaced were the hood, bumper, windshield, and the plastic underneath. 

If someone who knew how to fix this up could do it, this car would run great for another 50,000 miles at least. I took great care of it and want more than it going to waste. Email me and let me know if interested. I can provide pictures if needed or arrange a meeting.

1999 GMC Yukon Denali
Description:
$2000 firm need gone asap!


This post is very hard for me to type. I bought this truck nearly 2 years ago to restore. It was and still is in need of help. I bought it from a guy who didn't take care of it and sat for 2 and a half year's.åÊ

I bought it and did extensive work and put ALOT of money into it while it sat at a friend's house. I drove it home the oem exhaust piping fell off from the manifold while taking it on a short cruise that day. Parked it and started going to town on it. I did pace setter long tubes, accel ceramic plugs,ac Delco plugs,new cap and rotor,accel coil,new cam and crank sensor. Can't get any pulse to fire... might be out of timing. I put wayyy too much money I will NEVER get back out of it. I just need it out of my driveway.. sadly I lost interest in it.

I have well over 4k just in additional parts in it just as it sits. Here is a list of things I have done to it so far.

Put a motor in it from a 97 Tahoe with 112k miles.
All moog suspension parts.
New upper control arms,bushings, inner and outer tie rod ends,sway bar links. Leveling keys,helper springs,3"rear blocks.
Swapped a rear end.
New brakes,turned rotors.
E fans
Skyjacker shocks
Pace setter long tube headers
Accel ceramic plug wires
A.c. Delco plugs
Accel coil. Ok I'm forgetting alot at this moment but just get a Hold of me if interested. I will go threw literally everything with you.

It's sitting on 22" rims right now, tires good. I painted 2 of the rims black the other 2 need sanded down and finished. I have factory rims also. It also has 1"rear hub centric spacers in the rear and .75" in the front. New led tails..blacked out fronts.. needs a new front bumper and hood(hood has rust)åÊ

It's a 1999 original Denali w 230k miles so it's go it's flaws. Previous owner said trans was rebuilt at 150k. It is a solid truck, I just found something else I'd rather have. Price is firm. So please don't waste my time.. I'm telling you it has it's flaws but if someone would finish it it would be a solid nice truck.

Has front dif drop installed for the added lift. I honestly can keep going on and on about the truck but I'm going to leave this info to someone actually interested in it.åÊ

Idc if you buy it for parts. Just please don't waste my time.

Edit: I pulled the factory intake to carb it. But something serious has came up and I just need it out of my driveway.. .first person to bring me $2000 and a trailer gets it. Will not hold!!!
